    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A method of forming molten metal into long shapes narrow in cross-section, such as rods or sheets. Used particularly in the manufacture of steel for use in construction. Metal is passed between dual rollers revolving in opposite directions at uniform speed; the heat of the rollers increasing the plasticity of the metal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
